Cameron to Name Cooper New Strategy Director, Guardian Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-02-15T23:48:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/cameron-to-name-cooper-new-strategy-director-guardian-reports.html
U.K. Prime Minister  David Cameron 
will appoint Andrew Cooper, as Downing Street’s director of
strategy alongside Craig Oliver, recently appointed
communications director after the departure of  Andy Coulson , the
Guardian  reported , without attribution. Cooper is founder of the
polling company Populus and the former director of the  Conservative party ’s research department.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 